// ============================================================
// Block B4 — Performance routing (PATH-B FRAGMENT)
// ============================================================
//
// SCOPE FOR B4:
//   - Per-class topic-mastery routing for the AI generator: when a teacher
//     asks the AI to generate a paper for class X, prefer topics where
//     class X is historically weak.
//
// SCHEMA CHANGES: NONE.
//
// Mastery is computed *on the fly* from existing fields the schema
// already provides:
//
//   AnswerScript.autoCorrect       — boolean, set by the auto-grader
//                                    on submit for MCQ items.
//   AnswerScript.awardedMarks      — float, set by markers for
//                                    structured items (depends on B1
//                                    workflow; not yet used here).
//   PaperQuestion.question.primaryTopicId
//                                  — the topic this script's question
//                                    is tagged to.
//   ClassEnrollment.role='student' — the rows we filter by to know who
//                                    "the class" is.
//
// Because all the inputs already exist, B4 is a *service-only* fragment
// — there is no new Prisma model, no migration, and no path-b
// concatenation required for this block. The integrator can leave this
// file empty; it exists so the path-b-fragments directory has a slot
// for B4 in case a future iteration adds a materialised mastery table
// (e.g. for performance reasons at scale).
//
// FUTURE CONSIDERATIONS (not implemented now):
//   - A `ClassTopicMastery` materialised view, refreshed on submission
//     finalisation, would let us serve weakTopics in O(1). Today we
//     scan AnswerScript per-request, which is fine for class-sized
//     samples (<10k rows).
//   - Once B1 marker workflow lands, switch the mastery formula from
//     `mean(autoCorrect)` to `sum(awardedMarks) / sum(paperQuestion.marks)`
//     so structured items count too.
